Oxfam Website Content Summary

The following report is for the period between 2019-06-01 and 2019-07-09.

Effective 2019-06-01 we established a new metric for reporting website content engagement - Qualified Page Views.
For immersive stories a qualified page view is counted if any of the following happen:
1) a user spends 45 or more seconds on a page and scrolls through at least 50% of the page
2) a user spends 45 or more seconds on a page and views at least 50% of any audio or video elements on the page or
3) a user clicks a CTA.

For non-immersive stories a qualified page view is counted if any of the following happen:
1) a user spends 30 or more seconds on a page and scrolls through at least 50% of the page
2) a user spends 30 or more seconds on a page and views at least 50% of any audio or video elements on the page or
3) a user clicks a CTA.

Unique Page Views are the total number of unique page views for any given piece of content.
Qualified Page View Rate is the number of Qualified Page Views divided by the number of Unique Page Views and is expressed as a percentage.

Dataset Summary Statistics

This is a summary of the content-level data in this report.
For example, the average number of unique page views for a given piece of content in this dataset was: 20.
The 3rd Quartile (3rd Qu.) for unique page views of content in this dataset was 6. This means that 75% of the content in this data set had less than or equal to 3 unique page views.
The most number of unique page views any given content had was 3537. The least number of unique page views any given content had was 1.
